Type Parameters:
E - The type of element to contain in this queue
All Implemented Interfaces:
Groupable<E>, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, Queue<E>, RandomAccess
public class CircularQueue<E> extends GroupableList<E> implements Queue<E>
A circular queue. Entries can be added or removed concurrently to this queue.

      @Nullable public E next()

    • offer

      public boolean offer(E e)
      Adds the element to this queue. Since a circular queue has no limit to its size other than the limit of integers, this will only fail if the resulting queue's size will trigger an integer overflow.
